Frustrated Mango passengers have been left stranded on Wednesday. ACSA is not allowing the airline's planes to operate due to non-payment. For more on this story I'm joined by Benediction Zubane from Mango Airlines. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -Mango flights will resume on Thursday. This is after an agreement was reached with Airports Company South Africa. ACSA had suspended the airline's flights due to non-payment. READ: Mango flights suspended Passengers were stranded while discussions were underway to reach an agreement. This comes as embattled national carrier, South African Airways (SAA), remains in business rescue. Watch the video above for more details on this story